description.narrative: Good progress has been made this year on a number of areas: with ENAP project, 9% of new-born benefited from resuscitation, 25% of underweight children were successfully treated in kangaroo mother rooms, and the number of stillbirths in UNICEF supported facilities dropped to 2%; at community level, 70% of households with pregnancies received monthly visits; 91% of recorded home births received essential care; 94% pneumonia cases and 97% diarrhea cases were treated by CHWs; an Effective Vaccine Management Assessment was conducted in April 2019 with a composite score of 67%, a gain of 12 points compared to the 2014 assessment. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
